---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="For Sports Hotels"
  description="Avorix for sports hotels: half-board at your standard, group menus at scale, seasonal staff productive from day one. Cook app, training, and staff."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-28 pb-16 px-6 bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-50/50 to-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-sm font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-brand-500 mb-4">For Sports Hotels</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-neutral-900 leading-tight mb-6">Your Guests Perform. Your Kitchen Too. No Matter Who's Cooking.</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Half-board at your standard, group menus at scale, seasonal staff productive from day one: Avorix makes your sports hotel kitchen independent of whoever you found this season.
      </p>
      <a href="/en/contact" data-cta-location="sporthotels-hero" class="bg-brand-500 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-bold hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors inline-block">Book a Demo</a>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-4">Avorix holds an official staff leasing permit.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">Half-Board at Your Standard. With Half the Crew.</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Active guests forgive little.</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Someone who spent all day on the slopes or in the saddle expects a dinner that rounds off the day. Not just filling — good.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Groups blow up every routine.</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">A training camp with 40 athletes, special requests, dietary requirements. Plus the regular evening service. Without a system, it's a gamble.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Seasonal staff arrive without onboarding.</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">New people, new menu, no lead time. Yet everything has to be perfect from the first evening.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-6">When the kitchen wobbles, the reputation wobbles. And athletes talk — to each other, to coaches, to federations.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- System -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">The Avorix System: Three Building Blocks for a Kitchen That Holds Up.</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">1 &middot; The System</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Your menu is documented in the Cook App: recipes, steps, photos, quantities. Every team member works to the same standard.</p>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs mt-3">Incl. Portion Calculator: 120 instead of 80 portions today? The app scales automatically.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">2 &middot; Training</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">An Avorix chef trains your team on-site — right at the stove, with your dishes. Not in a seminar room, but in your kitchen.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">3 &middot; Reinforcement</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">When you're short on chefs, we provide them. Legally via staff leasing, onboarded through the system.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <a href="/en/contact" data-cta-location="sporthotels-system" class="border-2 border-brand-500 text-brand-500 px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-bold hover:bg-brand-50 transition-colors inline-block">How the Avorix System Works</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Group Menus -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Group Menus at Scale Are the Ideal Case for This System.</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Training camp menu sequences are plannable and reproducible. Three courses, 40 portions, fixed requirements — exactly what a system needs to shine.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        The Cook App scales quantities automatically. The processes are documented. And your team works through the steps instead of improvising. The result: consistent quality, whether 40 or 120 portions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Season Staff -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Chefs for the Season. Legally Sound. Productive From Day One.</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Avorix provides chefs via staff leasing — in Germany, Austria, and Tyrol. No bogus self-employment risk, no contract confusion. Our official staff leasing permit covers it.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        And because your kitchen is documented in the system, seasonal staff work to your standard from day one. No weeks of onboarding, no hoping it'll work out.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-4">The seasonal chef leaves, the knowledge stays — in the app, not in one person's head.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Before Season -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Before the Season Is the Best Time.</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        In the quiet weeks before the season starts, we document your menu, train your team, and build the system. When the first guests arrive, everything is in place.
      </p>
      <a href="/en/pilot-program" data-cta-location="sporthotels-pilot" class="bg-brand-500 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-bold hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors inline-block">To the Pilot Program</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <details open class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <summary class="font-bold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">We do a mix of buffet and set menus. Does that work?</summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-3">Yes. The Cook App documents both: buffet components just like menu sequences. The Portion Calculator scales to the respective guest count.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <summary class="font-bold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">How close to season start can we still begin?</summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-3">Ideally four to six weeks of lead time. In urgent cases, we can move faster — we prioritize the most important dishes and expand on an ongoing basis.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <summary class="font-bold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">Sports groups often have special dietary requests. Can the system handle that?</summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-3">Yes. Variations, allergies, and nutrition plans can be stored in the app. Your team sees the adjustments right at the station.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <summary class="font-bold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">Can we just get staff for the season, without the app?</summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-3">In principle, yes. But the system makes the biggest difference: seasonal staff are immediately productive because everything is documented. Without the system, onboarding takes weeks.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">The Next Season Is Coming. This Time With a System.</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">Let's have a quick conversation to see how Avorix fits into your kitchen.</p>
      <a href="/en/contact" data-cta-location="sporthotels-final" class="bg-brand-500 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-xl font-bold text-lg hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors inline-block">Book a Demo</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
